propCheckedIcon: The icon to display when the component is checked.
propClasses: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.
propColor: The color of the component. It supports those theme colors that make sense for this component.
propDisableRipple: If `true`, the ripple effect is disabled.
propEdge:
If given, uses a negative margin to counteract the padding on one
side (this is often helpful for aligning the left or right
side of the icon with content above or below, without ruining the border
size and shape).
propIcon: The icon to display when the component is unchecked.
propInputRef: Pass a ref to the `input` element.
propOnChange: Callback fired when the state is changed.
propSize:
The size of the switch.
`small` is equivalent to the dense switch styling.
propValue:
The value of the component. The DOM API casts this to a string.
The browser uses "on" as the default value.
stylesRoot: Styles applied to the root element.
stylesEdgeStart: Styles applied to the root element if `edge="start"`.
stylesEdgeEnd: Styles applied to the root element if `edge="end"`.
stylesSwitchBase: Styles applied to the internal `SwitchBase` component's `root` class.
stylesColorPrimary: Styles applied to the internal SwitchBase component's root element if `color="primary"`.
stylesColorSecondary: Styles applied to the internal SwitchBase component's root element if `color="secondary"`.
stylesSizeSmall: Styles applied to the root element if `size="small"`.
stylesChecked: Pseudo-class applied to the internal `SwitchBase` component's `checked` class.
stylesDisabled: Pseudo-class applied to the internal SwitchBase component's disabled class.
stylesInput: Styles applied to the internal SwitchBase component's input element.
stylesThumb: Styles used to create the thumb passed to the internal `SwitchBase` component `icon` prop.
stylesTrack: Styles applied to the track element.
